# AKFERP.Web — Tabler Admin Panel

## Theme reference

**Tabler — Premium and Open Source Admin Template (MIT)**
- Homepage: https://tabler.io
- Preview: https://preview.tabler.io
- Docs: https://tabler.io/docs
- GitHub: https://github.com/tabler/tabler
- Icons: https://tabler.io/icons (6000+)

When you need a new component pattern, look it up in the Tabler docs above and use plain HTML with Tabler/Bootstrap 5 CSS classes + `@tabler/icons-react`. Do NOT use any third-party React component library for UI.

## Stack

- `@tabler/core` (CSS/JS — Bootstrap 5 based), `@tabler/icons-react` (icon components).
- `react-chartjs-2` + `chart.js` for charts.
- React 18 + React Router 6 + Vite + TypeScript.
- CSS: Tabler bundled CSS (`@tabler/core/dist/css/tabler.min.css`) imported in `src/index.css`. Brand overrides via `--tblr-primary`.

## Brand

- ALKHIDMAT primary: `#0059A3` (`--tblr-primary`).
- Logo: `/alkhidmat-logo.png` in sidebar header and auth pages.
- Font: **Roboto** via Google Fonts in `index.html`.

## Dark mode

Tabler uses Bootstrap 5.3's `data-bs-theme` attribute on `<html>`.
- `document.documentElement.dataset.bsTheme = 'dark' | 'light'`
- ThemeContext handles preference (light/dark/system) and writes `data-bs-theme`.
- All Tabler components auto-adapt.

## Layout

```
div.page
  aside.navbar.navbar-vertical.navbar-expand-lg[data-bs-theme="dark"]   ← AppSidebar
  div.page-wrapper
    div.page-header.d-print-none                                        ← AppHeader
    div.page-body > div.container-xl > <Outlet />
    footer.footer.footer-transparent                                    ← AppFooter
```

- **`DefaultLayout`**: `AppSidebar` + `.page-wrapper` with `AppHeader`, `.page-body`, `AppFooter`.
- **`AppSidebar`**: Tabler vertical sidebar (`navbar-vertical navbar-expand-lg`). Uses `data-bs-theme="dark"` for dark sidebar (Bootstrap 5.3 attribute, NOT `navbar-dark` class). Brand in `<h1 class="navbar-brand navbar-brand-autodark">`. On mobile (<992px) overlays content with `.sidebar-overlay` backdrop, auto-closes on route change.
- **`AppSidebarNav`**: Dropdowns in vertical sidebar expand inline (not popups). Groups auto-open if a child route is active. Tabler CSS adds the toggle chevron automatically via `.dropdown-toggle`.
- **`AppHeader`**: Uses `div.page-header` (NOT a `<header>` navbar). Contains breadcrumb on the left, theme toggle + user dropdown on the right. Sidebar hamburger visible only on mobile (`d-lg-none`).
- **Auth/error pages** (`/login`, `/signup`, `/404`): `div.page.page-center` with `container.container-tight`. Outside `DefaultLayout`.
- Sidebar nav: `src/_nav.tsx` (array of `NavItemDef` objects with `label`, `to?`, `icon?`, `children?`, `isTitle?`).
- Breadcrumbs: `AppBreadcrumb.tsx` → `routeNames` map + `EDIT_PATTERNS` for dynamic `:id` routes. Uses Bootstrap `ol.breadcrumb`.

## Icons

Use `@tabler/icons-react`. Import individual icons:
```tsx
import { IconUser, IconPlus, IconSearch } from '@tabler/icons-react';
<IconUser size={20} />
```
Browse all 6000+ icons at https://tabler.io/icons.

## Charts

Use `react-chartjs-2` with `chart.js`. Register required scales/elements:
```tsx
import { Line, Bar, Doughnut, Pie } from 'react-chartjs-2';
import { Chart as ChartJS, CategoryScale, LinearScale, PointElement, LineElement, BarElement, ArcElement, Filler, Tooltip, Legend } from 'chart.js';
ChartJS.register(CategoryScale, LinearScale, PointElement, LineElement, BarElement, ArcElement, Filler, Tooltip, Legend);
```

