## CRUD page patterns (reference: Employee module)

### List page (`EmployeeListPage`)
- `div.card` > `.card-header` (title + Add button) > `.card-body.border-bottom.py-3` (filters).
- Filters: `.input-group.input-group-sm` search + `.form-select` dept/status + page size.
- `div.table-responsive` > `table.table.table-vcenter.card-table.table-striped`.
- `span.badge.bg-{color}` for status.
- `div.dropdown` for row actions (Edit/Delete) — toggle `.show` with state.
- `ul.pagination.pagination-sm` in `.card-footer`.
- `div.modal.modal-blur` for delete confirmation — toggle with state.

### Add / Edit form (`EmployeeForm`)
- Shared component, receives `existing?: Employee` prop.
- `ul.nav.nav-tabs` for multi-section forms (Personal, Job, Address).
- Tab panels toggled with state + `d-none` class.
- `input.form-control`, `select.form-select`, `textarea.form-control`, `.input-group` with icon prefixes.
- `.was-validated` on form + `.invalid-feedback` for validation.
- `div.alert.alert-success.alert-dismissible` for save confirmation.
- `.card-footer.text-muted.small` for contextual help.

### Data store
- In-memory store at `src/data/employees.ts` — swap for API calls later.
- `employeeStore.getAll()`, `.getById()`, `.add()`, `.update()`, `.remove()`.

## Routes

| Path | Page | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/` | HomePage | Welcome + feature cards |
| `/login` | LoginPage | Full-screen auth (page-center) |
| `/signup` | SignupPage | Full-screen registration (page-center) |
| `/404` | NotFoundPage | Error page (empty state) |
| `/admin/dashboard` | AdminDashboardPage | Stat cards + charts + table |
| `/admin/records` | AdminTablePage | Generic paginated table |
| `/admin/records/new` | AdminAddFormPage | Generic add form |
| `/admin/employees` | EmployeeListPage | Full CRUD list |
| `/admin/employees/new` | AddEmployeePage | Add employee (tabbed form) |
| `/admin/employees/:id/edit` | EditEmployeePage | Edit employee (tabbed form) |

## When adding a new CRUD module

1. Create types + data store in `src/data/`.
2. Create `ListPage`, `Form`, `AddPage`, `EditPage` in `src/pages/admin/<module>/`.
3. Add routes in `AppRoutes.tsx` under `/admin`.
4. Add nav entries in `src/_nav.tsx` (use `NavItemDef` type).
5. Add breadcrumb names in `AppBreadcrumb.tsx` `routeNames` + `EDIT_PATTERNS`.
6. Use only Tabler CSS classes — no third-party React UI components.
